It is unclear as to why you send the data using `ObjectOutputStream` if you already have the data as `byte[] filebytes`, as you could send `byte[]` directly. Obviously your sender/receiver code needs compatible encode/decode mechanism at each side if you switched from `ObjectOutputStream` to `byte[]`. 

Note also that using in-memory copies of large streams may risk `OutOfMemoryError` if the size of your Excel files increase, it is better to send large files as a stream not one huge chunk.

